The Presidential candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Alhaji Atiku Abubakar will arrive at Sani Abacha Stadium, Kano any moment from now for his presidential rally. Our re3porter said  Atiku had landed at Aminu Kano International Airport (MAKIA). The PDP presidential candidate was received by Kwankwasiyya National Leader, Senator Rabi’u Musa Kwankwaso and other top PDP officials. Soon after he arrived at the airport, Atiku headed to the Aminu Kano Center for Democratic Research and Trianing, Mambayya House for a special visit to the center. After the short visit to the center, Atiku moved to Kano emir’s palace to pay homage to Emir of Kano Muhammad Sanusi ll. Daily Trust gathered it was after the courtesy visit on the emir that Atiku would move to Sani Abacha stadium for the political rally. PDP supporters paint Kano red as they await Atiku's arrival 2019 Elections: Atiku leads campaign train to Kano today JUST IN: Atiku is free to campaign at Sani Abacha stadium